WEBVTT

00:03.253 --> 00:07.673
PlCARD:
Captain's log, stardate 42686.4.

00:07.841 --> 00:09.800
We are en route
to Starbase Montgomery

00:09.968 --> 00:12.386
for engineering consultations
prompted

00:12.554 --> 00:15.389
by minor readout anomalies.

00:18.101 --> 00:21.562
- l would consider them insignificant.
- What if you're wrong?

00:22.355 --> 00:23.897
Sorry.

00:24.065 --> 00:25.899
But what if it is more
than a mere discrepancy?

00:26.067 --> 00:28.944
- Then l'd say we have a problem.
- Agreed.

00:29.112 --> 00:32.072
We will have Starbase Montgomery
give us an independent reading.

00:32.240 --> 00:34.158
Even if the molecular level controls
have failed,

00:34.325 --> 00:37.494
we can still re-crystallize the dilithium
without outside help.

00:37.662 --> 00:40.456
Don't worry, Data.
My ego isn't at stake here.

00:40.623 --> 00:42.249
Perhaps we can reprogram
the system

00:42.417 --> 00:43.959
to correct the readout variables.

00:45.962 --> 00:47.171
That's certainly another option

00:47.338 --> 00:49.506
but as we are stopping
at Starbase Montgomery anyway,

00:49.674 --> 00:51.300
we'll let them do the analysis.

00:51.468 --> 00:54.845
l don't recall Starbase Montgomery
being on the mission itinerary.

00:55.263 --> 00:56.305
[PlCARD SlGHS]

00:56.473 --> 00:58.932
l think we could all use
a 1 2-hour layover.

00:59.100 --> 01:01.977
Besides, l've just received
some personnel transfer directives.

01:02.145 --> 01:03.729
Priority matter.

01:03.897 --> 01:04.938
Boarding or disembarking?

01:05.106 --> 01:06.607
WESLEY [OVER COM]:
Captain Picard?

01:06.775 --> 01:08.734
We're within hailing range
of Starbase Montgomery.

01:08.902 --> 01:10.611
Go to half impulse power.

01:10.779 --> 01:13.197
Uh, will you join me
in the observation lounge

01:13.364 --> 01:14.907
when you're done?

01:28.213 --> 01:29.797
Captain?

01:31.007 --> 01:33.467
Number One, l've just been
recollecting the arrival

01:33.635 --> 01:36.929
of a new first officer
onboard the Enterprise.

01:37.097 --> 01:41.308
And a manual docking
confidently achieved.

01:43.061 --> 01:46.522
l may have been somewhat
miserly in my congratulations then

01:46.689 --> 01:48.482
so let me make up for it now.

01:50.610 --> 01:54.905
The captain of the Starship Ares
is retiring.

01:55.448 --> 01:56.949
Congratulations.

01:57.117 --> 01:58.867
You've been selected
as his replacement.

01:59.035 --> 02:01.120
The Ares.
She's in the Vega-Omicron sector.

02:01.621 --> 02:05.916
Mm-hm. And they have picked up
indications of intelligent life-form

02:06.084 --> 02:07.876
though nothing confirmed.

02:08.044 --> 02:10.003
Obviously Starfleet
will want to know more.

02:10.171 --> 02:11.755
Well, that's why
they're asking for you.

02:11.923 --> 02:13.841
Not for your military proficiency,

02:14.008 --> 02:17.594
but for your skill as an explorer
and as a diplomat.

02:17.762 --> 02:18.804
Vega-Omicron.

02:18.972 --> 02:20.973
lt'll take months at high warp
just to get there.

02:21.516 --> 02:24.893
With no guarantee of finding anything
when you arrive.

02:25.061 --> 02:27.563
Well, you have 12 hours
to think it over.

02:27.730 --> 02:32.401
And if it's not too premature,
congratulations, captain.

02:34.320 --> 02:36.363
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

02:58.344 --> 03:02.472
PlCARD:
Space, the final frontier.

03:03.141 --> 03:07.144
These are the voyages
ofthe starship Enterprise.

03:07.312 --> 03:12.441
lts continuing mission:
to explore strange, new worlds,

03:13.109 --> 03:17.196
to seek out new life
and new civilizations,

03:17.697 --> 03:21.992
to boldly go where no one
has gone before.

04:30.770 --> 04:33.814
- Establish synchronous orbit.
- Aye, sir.

04:35.733 --> 04:38.652
Starbase Montgomery is sending
a civilian advisor onboard

04:38.820 --> 04:41.780
- to brief you on the Ares' mission.
- A personal briefing?

04:42.282 --> 04:45.158
Mm-hm. A strategic attachÃ©
with a specialized knowledge

04:45.326 --> 04:46.368
in the frontier regions.

04:46.536 --> 04:49.246
l think you'll find the briefing
interesting.

04:50.456 --> 04:51.707
l hope it's complete.

04:51.874 --> 04:53.959
Much of my decision
will be based on it.

04:54.127 --> 04:56.920
ENSlGN [OVER COM]: Commander
Riker to Transporter Room 3.

04:58.298 --> 05:00.090
Enjoy.

05:06.806 --> 05:07.931
Ensign?

05:08.099 --> 05:11.601
Ah, you're right on time, commander.
He's on his way now.

05:18.985 --> 05:20.319
Dad.

05:22.989 --> 05:26.283
You're the civilian advisor,
the strategic attachÃ©?

05:26.451 --> 05:28.201
l asked Captain Picard
to keep it quiet.

05:28.369 --> 05:30.620
l didn't wanna make you nervous,
excited.

05:31.164 --> 05:34.624
lt's been 1 5 years. Excitement
is hardly the appropriate emotion.

05:36.252 --> 05:37.711
You've done well.

05:37.879 --> 05:41.673
First officer on the Enterprise,
quite a feather in your cap.

05:41.841 --> 05:43.633
l've worked hard.

05:44.677 --> 05:47.929
Of course. l'm proud of you, son.

05:48.473 --> 05:50.766
lf you'll excuse me,
l've got my duties to attend to.

05:51.768 --> 05:54.686
When you've settled in,
we can complete our briefing.

05:54.854 --> 05:57.689
Have security arrange an escort
for this gentleman.

05:57.857 --> 05:59.191
ENSlGN:
Aye, sir.

06:09.827 --> 06:11.203
Worf? Did you hear about

06:11.371 --> 06:12.788
- Commander Riker's promotion?
- Yes.

06:12.955 --> 06:15.123
He didn't know his father was coming.
He was surprised.

06:15.291 --> 06:16.917
- So?
- lmagine if it was your father.

06:17.085 --> 06:18.293
l never knew my father.

06:18.461 --> 06:20.295
l didn't have a father
long enough to know him.

06:20.463 --> 06:23.215
lt is a waste of time
to think of such things.

06:23.383 --> 06:25.884
l wasn't thinking about it
but everybody needs somebody.

06:26.052 --> 06:27.844
Enough!

06:32.433 --> 06:34.476
[CHATTERlNG]

06:36.896 --> 06:39.398
You know, Starbase Montgomery
really didn't have to send me help

06:39.565 --> 06:41.817
because l've already checked
the entire dilithium spectrum

06:41.984 --> 06:45.570
for anomalous frequencies, so you
don't have to waste your time on that.

06:46.114 --> 06:47.572
[LA FORGE SlGHS]

06:47.907 --> 06:50.242
Wes, are you okay?

06:51.077 --> 06:53.662
- l was just talking to Worf.
- And?

06:53.830 --> 06:57.999
- He's really eccentric at times.
- That's one word for it.

06:58.167 --> 07:00.419
He was really upset.

07:00.586 --> 07:02.212
l must have said something wrong.

07:02.380 --> 07:04.214
Maybe Worf's just not thrilled
with the prospect

07:04.382 --> 07:06.425
of losing Commander Riker
to a new assignment.

07:06.592 --> 07:09.261
- l know l'm not.
- Neither am l.

07:09.429 --> 07:11.513
But with Worf,
it was something else.

07:11.681 --> 07:15.517
- Something's really bothering him.
- Think so, huh?

07:17.728 --> 07:20.105
[CHATTERlNG]

07:28.072 --> 07:30.240
- Female?
- No.

07:30.408 --> 07:33.660
Career?

07:34.370 --> 07:37.122
- Family.
- That is trouble.

07:37.290 --> 07:40.041
You choose your enemies
and you choose your friends.

07:40.209 --> 07:45.380
- But family, heh, that's in the stars.
- So l've heard.

07:52.847 --> 07:54.181
MAN 1 :
Kyle Riker.

07:54.348 --> 07:56.224
Excuse me, ladies.

07:57.977 --> 07:59.895
Great to see you.

08:02.523 --> 08:05.859
MAN 2:
Kyle, been a long time.

08:18.831 --> 08:22.584
This is more than a surprise.
lt's total shock.

08:22.752 --> 08:24.461
You mean,
you didn't bake me a cake?

08:24.670 --> 08:26.004
[CHUCKLES]

08:26.172 --> 08:29.299
- You're actually here.
- That makes two of us.

08:29.467 --> 08:31.885
- How about a drink?
- How about a kiss?

08:32.678 --> 08:34.888
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

08:36.224 --> 08:37.933
They know each other.

08:38.100 --> 08:40.185
No kidding. Well, l know her too.

08:40.353 --> 08:42.646
But we don't do that.

08:49.362 --> 08:51.613
KYLE:
You look wonderful.

08:59.121 --> 09:00.163
And it has nothing to do

09:00.331 --> 09:02.040
with Commander Riker's
new assignment?

09:02.208 --> 09:04.668
No, his reaction
was just the opposite of mine.

09:04.835 --> 09:06.795
- Completely unaffected.
LA FORGE: You see, Wes?

09:06.963 --> 09:09.422
With all that's going on,
maybe you're overreacting.

09:09.590 --> 09:10.966
Really?

09:11.133 --> 09:13.093
You try talking to Worf, Geordi.

09:13.261 --> 09:15.762
l'm telling you,
he is not normal for Worf.

09:17.515 --> 09:19.182
There is of course
a genetic predisposition

09:19.350 --> 09:21.434
toward hostility among all Klingons.

09:21.602 --> 09:24.771
But Worf has been unusually
out of sorts.

09:25.314 --> 09:27.607
Come on,
he's never been much on charm.

09:28.484 --> 09:31.278
Well, whatever is troubling him,
l think we should try to help.

09:31.445 --> 09:35.282
- He is our friend.
- l for one wanna keep him friendly.

09:35.449 --> 09:36.866
Suggestions?

09:37.034 --> 09:38.702
Empirical study.

09:38.869 --> 09:40.662
- Monitor the subject.
WESLEY: Right.

09:40.830 --> 09:43.832
Watch the subject for any signs
of unusual behavior.

09:44.000 --> 09:45.041
That won't be difficult.

09:45.209 --> 09:47.210
Within the norm of Klingon patterns,
of course.

09:47.378 --> 09:51.381
- Discretion will be required.
- Agreed. When do we start?

09:53.342 --> 09:57.387
We will assist you as needed.
You found the problem.

09:57.555 --> 09:59.806
And you must solve it.

10:16.782 --> 10:17.949
Thank you.

10:18.117 --> 10:22.370
And after working out the Fuurinkazan
battle strategies at the Tokyo Base,

10:22.538 --> 10:25.540
l was asked to come here to work
for Starfleet as a tactical advisor.

10:25.708 --> 10:28.251
l'm surprised you stayed out of action
as long as you did.

10:28.419 --> 10:30.170
Will, please join us.

10:30.338 --> 10:32.088
Your father and l
are just catching up.

10:32.256 --> 10:33.757
You never told me you knew him.

10:34.717 --> 10:38.094
Well, it wasn't exactly a secret.

10:38.262 --> 10:39.929
lt just never really came up.

10:40.598 --> 10:41.765
Sit down, son.

10:42.266 --> 10:44.017
l'm ready for that briefing
whenever you are.

10:58.324 --> 11:00.492
- lt was a pleasure.
KYLE: Good to see you too, Graham.

11:00.660 --> 11:02.327
GRAHAM:
Mm-hm.

11:03.245 --> 11:05.288
You wouldn't be running for mayor,
would you?

11:05.456 --> 11:07.457
Do pick-up work
for the Federation long enough

11:07.625 --> 11:09.376
and it'll happen to you too.

11:11.671 --> 11:13.630
l thought about you a lot.

11:13.798 --> 11:17.008
Kyle, l don't need to hear
what you don't need to say.

11:17.176 --> 11:18.843
We could have been great together.

11:19.595 --> 11:20.845
Possibly.

11:21.013 --> 11:25.100
- ls it true you got married?
- Again. And again.

11:25.267 --> 11:27.227
That makes you three for three,
doesn't it?

11:27.770 --> 11:28.812
l'm not complaining.

11:28.979 --> 11:31.356
Each was a good man
and we're all still good friends.

11:31.524 --> 11:34.984
- Like us?
- Close, but different.

11:35.152 --> 11:37.195
They were all a little more in touch
with themselves.

11:37.363 --> 11:39.239
Ah. Ouch.

11:39.407 --> 11:40.865
Face facts, Kyle. You're crusty.

11:41.033 --> 11:44.285
You have a reputation for being hard
as nails and getting the job done.

11:44.453 --> 11:46.913
But underneath it all,
you're not so bad.

11:47.456 --> 11:49.082
Some of us even love you.

11:51.585 --> 11:53.670
And then there's Will.

11:57.091 --> 11:59.300
Then there's Will.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.974
You know, Wesley should really
be doing this on his own.

12:06.142 --> 12:07.392
But he needs his study time.

12:07.560 --> 12:08.601
[LA FORGE SCOFFS]

12:08.769 --> 12:11.020
l can't believe you fell for that.

12:15.401 --> 12:18.403
l don't know, Data,
he looks perfectly normal to me.

12:18.571 --> 12:22.407
ln solitude there is nothing to trigger
unusual behavior.

12:22.575 --> 12:26.035
Good point.
Let's not tamper with the status quo.

12:26.203 --> 12:29.706
But that would defeat the opportunity
for our behavioral research.

12:29.874 --> 12:31.875
ln all probability,

12:32.042 --> 12:33.877
he is simply lonely.

12:34.044 --> 12:37.797
We can relieve his anxiety
through socialization.

12:38.549 --> 12:40.675
Be my guest.

12:48.100 --> 12:50.351
Excuse me, lieutenant.

12:50.519 --> 12:54.481
You seem to have lost the will
to communicate with others.

12:54.648 --> 12:57.734
You have friends here. We--

12:58.736 --> 13:00.737
We care about you.

13:00.905 --> 13:03.531
Why, just recently,
Geordi, Wesley and l were saying--

13:03.699 --> 13:08.119
With all due respect, be gone!

13:10.498 --> 13:11.539
Sir.

13:25.471 --> 13:29.140
He seems quite sincere
in his desire for solitude.

13:29.308 --> 13:31.309
Seeing is believing, huh?

13:50.037 --> 13:51.120
[DOOR CHlMES]

13:51.288 --> 13:52.705
Come in.

13:54.750 --> 13:56.167
Worf.

13:56.335 --> 13:58.044
May l have a moment, sir?

13:58.754 --> 13:59.963
Of course, what is it?

14:00.506 --> 14:03.341
lt is very difficult to say.

14:03.509 --> 14:06.970
Words are not always easy for me.

14:09.014 --> 14:10.640
ls that Earth?

14:10.808 --> 14:14.102
Yes, Alaska. l was 9 years old.

14:14.270 --> 14:16.521
That is a fish you are holding.

14:18.482 --> 14:20.483
And l didn't even catch it.

14:21.986 --> 14:24.529
- But it looks like you were--
- Hooked it.

14:24.697 --> 14:26.990
My father took the rod away.
Wouldn't let me reel it in.

14:27.157 --> 14:29.158
He was afraid that l would lose it.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.621
You do not have good feelings
for your father?

14:34.623 --> 14:36.624
No, l...

14:36.792 --> 14:38.459
Well...

14:38.627 --> 14:40.920
l'm not sure what l'm feeling.

14:41.714 --> 14:42.755
What's on your mind?

14:48.095 --> 14:50.263
You plan to leave the Enterprise?

14:50.431 --> 14:52.140
l've been offered my own command.

14:53.434 --> 14:55.810
l would like to join you.

14:59.815 --> 15:02.025
l haven't accepted
the assignment yet.

15:02.192 --> 15:04.193
But, sir,
it could be a dangerous mission.

15:04.361 --> 15:05.904
There may be the potential
for combat.

15:06.071 --> 15:07.614
That is not the purpose
of the mission.

15:07.781 --> 15:11.159
- Still, to die a true hero--
- Worf.

15:11.785 --> 15:13.328
You've made your point.

15:15.915 --> 15:18.791
Then l know
you will do the right thing.

15:35.684 --> 15:37.518
Finally, we're alone.

15:37.686 --> 15:39.562
Maybe now we can talk.

15:39.730 --> 15:41.856
l'm here for the briefing, sir.

15:45.027 --> 15:47.278
All you need to know is here.

15:51.575 --> 15:53.993
These mission details
could have been transmitted.

15:55.204 --> 15:58.081
l've been hearing some good things
about you.

15:58.248 --> 16:00.667
Then why haven't l heard from you?

16:01.168 --> 16:04.837
l know. Keeping in touch
is not my strong suit.

16:05.005 --> 16:07.173
lt's a funny thing
about being a parent.

16:07.341 --> 16:09.217
There aren't any tech manuals.

16:09.385 --> 16:12.387
No quick readouts to get you through
the next set of variables.

16:12.554 --> 16:15.181
You just gotta wing it
from day to day.

16:16.433 --> 16:20.061
- Will, when your mother died--
- Excuse me.

16:20.229 --> 16:22.605
l've gotta study this mission briefing.

16:23.273 --> 16:24.357
Will.

16:25.401 --> 16:28.319
l came to the Enterprise because...

16:30.072 --> 16:33.324
Look, considering where
you might be going, l wanted to...

16:35.536 --> 16:38.037
l'm here with my hand out, son.

16:59.143 --> 17:00.184
Poor guy.

17:00.352 --> 17:03.104
Picked up the flu virus
at our last stop at Nasreldine.

17:03.272 --> 17:04.939
Sounds nasty. What's the therapy?

17:05.107 --> 17:10.695
Tryptophan-lysine distillates,
with a generous dose of P.C.S.

17:10.863 --> 17:13.614
- P.C.S.?
- Pulaski's chicken soup.

17:13.782 --> 17:14.949
[KYLE CHUCKLES]

17:15.117 --> 17:16.659
You haven't lost your touch,
have you?

17:16.827 --> 17:19.370
l like to help. When they hurt, l hurt.

17:19.538 --> 17:23.833
TROl: Doctor Pulaski's greatest
medical skill is her empathy.

17:24.001 --> 17:25.835
You must be
Commander Riker's father.

17:26.003 --> 17:27.253
Yes, but how--?

17:27.421 --> 17:30.840
We've all heard about you
and l felt certain things.

17:31.008 --> 17:33.342
This is Deanna Troi,
ship's counselor.

17:34.678 --> 17:37.138
- Kyle Riker.
- l thought you two should meet.

17:37.306 --> 17:39.891
Deanna's job is to keep us
from deluding ourselves.

17:40.684 --> 17:43.102
Let me guess. Betazoid.

17:43.270 --> 17:45.229
At your service.

17:45.397 --> 17:48.232
l have some lab work to do.
lf you'll excuse me.

17:48.442 --> 17:52.153
Uh, why do l get the feeling
that this is a setup?

17:52.321 --> 17:57.033
Because you're intelligent,
wise and quite correct.

17:57.201 --> 18:01.162
Well, l've never been set up better,
that's for sure.

18:01.330 --> 18:04.707
You're also very anxious
about something.

18:07.127 --> 18:09.003
lt's Will, isn't it?

18:10.089 --> 18:12.548
You're not as close to him
as you'd like to be.

18:13.175 --> 18:14.675
Oh, l don't know.

18:14.843 --> 18:18.554
We both have pretty good taste
in women, wouldn't you say?

18:21.558 --> 18:24.560
l'd like to help you, if l can.

18:24.728 --> 18:28.356
- lf you'll let me.
- Fine. What is it you want from me?

18:28.524 --> 18:31.901
l came here to bury the hatchet
with my son,

18:32.069 --> 18:35.696
only to find out
that the ground was frozen solid.

18:35.864 --> 18:39.283
You don't seem to be the kind
to give up so easily.

18:39.451 --> 18:42.120
l didn't say l was giving up.

18:42.371 --> 18:45.414
lt would just be nice
to get a little something from him.

18:45.582 --> 18:48.334
- What is it you want from him?
- l don't know.

18:48.502 --> 18:50.211
Acknowledgement maybe or...

18:50.379 --> 18:53.840
Respect is earned, not bestowed.

18:54.007 --> 18:57.468
Respect? l don't need that from him.

18:58.804 --> 19:01.055
Perhaps you want him
to be proud of you.

19:01.223 --> 19:03.558
You carry great pride
in his accomplishments.

19:03.725 --> 19:07.895
Absolutely, look at him.
First officer of the Enterprise.

19:08.063 --> 19:10.314
Just been offered his first command.

19:10.482 --> 19:14.235
- Yet you covet his success.
- Please.

19:14.403 --> 19:16.195
He'd be lucky to have the career
l've had.

19:16.363 --> 19:19.240
True, you're well respected
in your field.

19:19.408 --> 19:22.201
l may have something of a reputation
for excellence.

19:22.369 --> 19:24.453
And false humility.

19:27.249 --> 19:30.835
My guess is that Will finds you
pretty fascinating.

19:31.003 --> 19:34.046
Candor seems to be a trait
he admires.

19:35.132 --> 19:38.176
Honesty is the trait he admires most.

19:39.303 --> 19:41.137
And you should honestly consider

19:41.305 --> 19:44.265
why you're so competitive
with your own son.

19:45.809 --> 19:47.602
Competitive?

19:48.145 --> 19:50.104
Maybe in the past.

19:50.272 --> 19:52.523
But l've come here
to help Will prepare

19:52.691 --> 19:55.610
for his first task as captain.

19:55.777 --> 19:58.529
Are you sure he'll accept
such a dangerous assignment?

19:58.697 --> 20:01.157
He'll accept it
just because it is dangerous.

20:01.325 --> 20:03.242
How can you be so sure?

20:03.410 --> 20:05.161
Because l would.

20:05.829 --> 20:08.998
And we aren't so different,
Will and l.

20:17.257 --> 20:18.674
[DOOR CHlMES]

20:18.842 --> 20:20.426
Come in.

20:23.013 --> 20:25.014
Ah.
You've seen your mission briefing?

20:25.182 --> 20:26.474
Yes, l have.

20:26.642 --> 20:28.684
- Any questions?
- No.

20:28.852 --> 20:31.229
Other than a question
about the Ares'first officer.

20:31.396 --> 20:33.898
- Oh, yes, his name is Flaherty.
- Yes.

20:34.066 --> 20:37.860
The briefing mentioned something
about an uncanny linguistic skill.

20:38.570 --> 20:40.112
That is an understatement,
Number One.

20:40.280 --> 20:42.156
The last time
l saw Commander Flaherty,

20:42.324 --> 20:43.908
he spoke 40 languages.

20:44.076 --> 20:46.619
As l recall, among the more exotic

20:46.787 --> 20:52.124
were Romulan, Klingon,
Giamon, Stroyerian.

20:52.292 --> 20:53.668
He speaks 40 languages?

20:53.835 --> 20:57.421
He has this unique ability
of instantaneously interpreting

20:57.589 --> 21:00.549
and extrapolating any verbal
communication that he hears.

21:00.717 --> 21:04.053
You will find him very useful
in Sector Vega-Omicron.

21:04.221 --> 21:05.263
Yes, l'm sure l will.

21:05.430 --> 21:06.472
[DOOR CHlMES]

21:06.640 --> 21:08.099
Come in.

21:08.600 --> 21:11.435
Oh, Captain Picard, at last.

21:11.603 --> 21:14.522
l'd like to thank you
for all the help you've been to my son.

21:14.690 --> 21:18.526
My only regret is
that your reunion marks Will's farewell.

21:18.694 --> 21:22.780
- But he's ready for this command?
- Oh, yes, l have no doubt.

21:24.366 --> 21:26.993
Captain, may l have a word
with my son?

21:27.160 --> 21:29.912
Yes, of course.
Excuse me, gentlemen.

21:33.917 --> 21:35.960
l won't be pushed into this decision.

21:36.128 --> 21:38.296
Oh, come on, Will.

21:38.463 --> 21:41.299
Don't you think you're ready
for the Ares?

21:42.009 --> 21:43.050
Starfleet does.

21:43.218 --> 21:45.886
Of course, because you're the best
candidate for the job.

21:47.264 --> 21:50.099
l only want you to know l'm here
if you need me.

21:50.267 --> 21:53.936
l've been on my own since l was 1 5.
l can take care of myself.

21:54.104 --> 21:56.981
Please, spare me the pain
of your childhood.

21:57.941 --> 22:02.361
l hung in for 1 3 years.
lf that wasn't enough, it's just too bad.

22:11.663 --> 22:13.998
Data, what if l missed something?

22:14.166 --> 22:16.208
The ship's computer
would have corrected immediately.

22:16.376 --> 22:18.002
Yeah, but maybe my inputs
were incorrect.

22:18.170 --> 22:21.422
Data, Geordi,
l figured out Worf's problem.

22:21.590 --> 22:22.631
You spoke to him?

22:22.799 --> 22:25.885
No, no, l accessed the complete
Klingon cultural database.

22:26.053 --> 22:29.472
- lt took me some time--
- Okay, Wesley, slow down.

22:29.639 --> 22:32.141
What is the problem?

22:32.309 --> 22:34.769
lt's the 1 0th anniversary
of Worf's Age of Ascension.

22:35.479 --> 22:38.230
- His what?
- The Klingon Age of Ascension.

22:38.398 --> 22:40.107
lt's a ritual of great significance.

22:40.275 --> 22:42.151
A rite of initiation
marking the new level

22:42.319 --> 22:44.153
of Klingon spiritual attainment.

22:44.321 --> 22:47.490
And what is the significance
of the anniversary of this event?

22:47.657 --> 22:50.993
lt's a day of celebration and rituals
spent with one's fellow Klingons.

22:51.161 --> 22:53.245
Worf doesn't have
any Klingon friends.

22:53.955 --> 22:54.997
We're his friends.

22:55.165 --> 22:56.957
Right, but we don't practice
Klingon tradition

22:57.125 --> 22:58.876
and we're not Klingons.

22:59.044 --> 23:02.004
Worf is feeling culturally
and socially isolated.

23:02.589 --> 23:03.964
So, what are you suggesting?

23:04.132 --> 23:07.218
l mean, l'm not sure l wanna invite
a bunch of Klingons onboard.

23:07.386 --> 23:10.805
We can program the ship's computer
to supply simulations on the Holodeck.

23:10.972 --> 23:14.183
Holographic Klingons?
Sure, why not?

23:14.351 --> 23:15.726
We need only
to program the computer

23:15.894 --> 23:17.770
with details of the specific ceremony.

23:17.938 --> 23:21.440
Now, the cultural database said
that the Klingon's family must attend.

23:21.608 --> 23:24.360
So? We're his family. We'll go.

23:24.528 --> 23:28.697
l just wonder what kind of party
the Klingons had in mind.

23:33.745 --> 23:35.246
Have you got a minute?

23:35.414 --> 23:36.705
Sure.

23:36.873 --> 23:39.208
l wanted to apologize for my remark
in Ten-Forward.

23:39.376 --> 23:41.710
Your personal life
is none of my business.

23:42.462 --> 23:47.133
- Even if it involves your father?
- Even if it involves my father.

23:48.427 --> 23:51.345
Did he ever tell you
why he never remarried?

23:51.513 --> 23:53.722
What woman would have him
with an ego like that?

23:54.724 --> 23:58.060
l would have. ln a cold minute.

24:09.531 --> 24:12.867
Twelve years ago,
Kyle Riker was a civilian strategist

24:13.034 --> 24:16.579
advising Starfleet
in its conflict with the Tholians.

24:16.746 --> 24:18.831
The starbase
that he was operating from

24:18.999 --> 24:20.040
was attacked.

24:20.208 --> 24:22.501
None of the base crew
was expected to live.

24:22.669 --> 24:26.839
And they all died.
All except your father.

24:28.258 --> 24:31.760
Your father alone
had the will to endure,

24:31.928 --> 24:34.305
to face the pain, to live.

24:35.849 --> 24:38.017
l never knew any of that about him.

24:39.269 --> 24:44.064
l've never seen a man fight so hard
in all my life.

24:44.483 --> 24:47.860
- And you fell in love?
- Yes.

24:48.028 --> 24:49.987
And so did he.

24:51.907 --> 24:53.949
But marriage
was out of the question.

24:54.117 --> 24:57.036
- He had other priorities.
- His career.

24:59.039 --> 25:02.750
You know, if l were you,
going out on the Ares,

25:02.918 --> 25:06.921
l'd jettison the emotional baggage
you're still carrying around.

25:17.390 --> 25:20.392
Now, the Klingon cultural database
was very specific on the setting.

25:20.560 --> 25:21.685
Now, let me guess.

25:21.853 --> 25:24.522
Twenty-piece orchestra,
magnificent ballroom,

25:24.689 --> 25:25.731
everyone in formal wear.

25:25.899 --> 25:29.276
Now, there is some unusual test
of inner strength involved.

25:29.444 --> 25:31.445
That would entail the use
of Klingon pain sticks.

25:31.613 --> 25:33.948
Pain sticks? Sounds lovely.

25:34.115 --> 25:38.035
Enduring physical suffering
is considered a Klingon spiritual test.

25:38.203 --> 25:40.371
You mean, in order for Worf
to celebrate the anniversary

25:40.539 --> 25:43.499
of this ascension,
he has to be hurt?

25:43.667 --> 25:45.834
And we have to witness this?

25:46.002 --> 25:47.670
We are his family.

25:53.593 --> 25:54.635
[DOOR CHlMES]

25:54.803 --> 25:56.095
Come.

25:58.348 --> 26:00.015
Number One.

26:00.934 --> 26:03.686
l'd be a fool to turn
that promotion down, wouldn't l?

26:04.437 --> 26:05.980
l don't know.

26:06.731 --> 26:09.233
And if you're asking me
what l think you should do,

26:09.734 --> 26:11.110
l don't know that either.

26:14.197 --> 26:18.826
l can spell out for you, albeit crudely,
what you're choosing between.

26:19.202 --> 26:23.080
As the first officer of the Enterprise,
you have a position of distinction,

26:23.248 --> 26:27.042
prestige, even glamour of a sort.

26:28.378 --> 26:32.256
You are the second in command
of Starfleet's flagship.

26:32.424 --> 26:34.550
But still second in command.

26:36.720 --> 26:42.349
Your promotion will transfer you
to a relatively insignificant ship

26:42.517 --> 26:46.020
in an obscure corner of the galaxy.

26:47.022 --> 26:49.690
But it will be your ship,

26:50.483 --> 26:52.943
and being who you are,

26:53.111 --> 26:57.656
it will soon be vibrant
with your authority, your style,

26:58.283 --> 26:59.908
your vision.

27:03.038 --> 27:04.622
You know,

27:06.082 --> 27:09.585
there really is no substitute
for holding the reins.

27:15.300 --> 27:19.470
l'll need a little more time
to make this decision.

27:35.111 --> 27:37.488
- Find anything yet?
- Not yet.

27:37.656 --> 27:39.365
There is nothing to find.

27:39.908 --> 27:43.535
- No harm in checking, l guess.
- Really?

27:43.703 --> 27:46.497
How would you like them to give
the transporter operation a once-over?

27:46.665 --> 27:50.668
- No problem. We're totally ship-shape.
- You're missing the point.

27:50.835 --> 27:53.879
lt's just the idea
that they even suspect a malfunction.

27:54.047 --> 27:56.048
lf l were not
a consummate professional

27:56.216 --> 27:57.299
and an android,

27:57.467 --> 28:00.803
l would find this entire procedure
insulting.

28:01.429 --> 28:03.222
Thanks, Data.

28:03.640 --> 28:05.140
[LA FORGE SlGHS]

28:08.561 --> 28:11.188
Chief, would you be able
to attend a little party

28:11.356 --> 28:13.107
for Lieutenant Worf at 1 700 hours?

28:13.274 --> 28:15.067
Party for Worf?

28:15.235 --> 28:18.487
- Sounds intriguing. l'd be delighted.
- lt's a surprise.

28:18.655 --> 28:21.073
My lips are sealed.

28:24.327 --> 28:26.453
l didn't wanna leave
without saying goodbye.

28:27.205 --> 28:29.248
l don't like goodbyes.

28:29.416 --> 28:31.500
How about until next time?

28:32.043 --> 28:34.002
How about until next time.

28:35.380 --> 28:39.258
lt's been a pleasure working with you,
commander.

28:39.426 --> 28:42.511
The feeling is mutual, counselor.

28:42.679 --> 28:45.806
l'm supposed to know
how everyone feels,

28:45.974 --> 28:48.559
but l can't read you right now.

28:48.727 --> 28:51.311
Perhaps your own feelings
are getting in the way.

28:51.896 --> 28:54.940
My job is to help others
sort out their emotions.

28:55.108 --> 28:57.818
My own feelings
are beside the point.

28:59.028 --> 29:00.779
Not to me.

29:01.281 --> 29:03.991
Our feelings
are what make us all human.

29:06.619 --> 29:08.954
Are you feeling sad?

29:15.044 --> 29:16.879
Yes, l am.

29:17.672 --> 29:19.590
So am l.

29:41.112 --> 29:44.364
l'm leaving at 21 00 hours.
Can l have a minute?

29:50.872 --> 29:52.539
l've practiced
my best academy courtesy.

29:52.707 --> 29:54.082
Now it's time for you to go.

29:54.250 --> 29:57.628
lt's time for us to have a talk.
So lower your shields.

29:57.796 --> 30:01.215
- l'm asking you to leave or l'll--
- Or you'll what?

30:01.382 --> 30:04.885
You know, it's a shame
there's no anbo-jyutsu ring nearby.

30:05.053 --> 30:07.721
Really? There is.
Deck 12, the gymnasium.

30:07.889 --> 30:10.891
We could clear the air
once and for all.

30:11.059 --> 30:12.351
You're on.

30:21.152 --> 30:24.696
Ah. Scuttlebutt says you wanted
to see me.

30:24.864 --> 30:26.657
That's right.

30:28.827 --> 30:30.911
l thought l knew you, Kyle.

30:31.079 --> 30:32.996
You do, as well as anyone.

30:33.164 --> 30:36.667
Then what is this l hear about
an anbo-jyutsu match with Will?

30:37.794 --> 30:38.836
You've heard?

30:39.003 --> 30:40.462
Haven't we grown beyond the point

30:40.630 --> 30:44.383
where we resolve our problems
with physical conflict?

30:44.551 --> 30:47.511
- l think you're overreacting.
- l'm overreacting?

30:47.679 --> 30:49.805
You're the one that's going out to fight
with his son.

30:49.973 --> 30:53.183
Don't think of it as a fight, Kate.
Think of it as more of a contest.

30:53.351 --> 30:57.729
- And suppose one of you is injured?
- l know where to find a good doctor.

30:57.897 --> 30:59.731
- Kate--
- Kyle.

31:00.525 --> 31:02.067
Will and l
have been playing anbo-jyutsu

31:02.235 --> 31:03.485
ever since he was 8 years old

31:03.653 --> 31:05.487
and he knows how to take care
of himself.

31:05.655 --> 31:07.030
And so do l.

31:07.198 --> 31:10.993
Don't take this personally,
but Will is in his prime.

31:11.160 --> 31:13.662
And l'm no spring chicken. l know.

31:13.830 --> 31:17.416
Don't worry.
He's never been able to beat me.

31:39.147 --> 31:40.814
Computer,

31:41.441 --> 31:43.108
is this it?

31:43.776 --> 31:47.821
COMPUTER: Correct,
Klingon Rite of Ascension Chamber.

31:48.364 --> 31:50.365
ls this really necessary?

31:50.533 --> 31:52.951
lf we wanna get Worf
through his problem, it is.

31:53.119 --> 31:57.956
Computer, please give us Klingon
personnel appropriate to this event.

32:00.293 --> 32:02.377
These images
have been specifically programmed

32:02.545 --> 32:04.796
for ascension rites.

32:05.340 --> 32:07.341
Cute bunch.

32:10.053 --> 32:11.845
And they use those?

32:12.013 --> 32:15.098
Those are Klingon pain sticks.

32:16.059 --> 32:21.188
l once saw one of them used
against a 2-ton Rectyne monopod.

32:21.356 --> 32:25.067
Poor creature jumped 5 meters
at the slightest touch.

32:25.234 --> 32:29.071
Finally died
from excessive cephalic pressures.

32:29.864 --> 32:32.240
- You mean--
- That's right.

32:32.408 --> 32:36.662
- The animal's head exploded like--
- l think that's enough, Chief O'Brien.

32:44.253 --> 32:48.298
- l do not enjoy riddles, counselor.
- You will enjoy this one.

32:48.466 --> 32:52.052
l'm in no mood for trifling or games.
Not today.

32:52.220 --> 32:54.805
l know what an important day
this is for you.

32:54.973 --> 32:57.474
The anniversary
of your Rite of Ascension.

32:57.642 --> 32:59.226
You know about that?

32:59.394 --> 33:01.311
All your friends onboard do.

33:02.146 --> 33:06.149
That is impossible.
lt is a secret known only to Klingons.

33:06.317 --> 33:09.361
And certain resourceful
young ensigns.

33:12.532 --> 33:15.033
Wesley Crusher.

33:15.201 --> 33:16.702
What does he know about it?

33:17.745 --> 33:19.454
Just bear with me.

33:19.622 --> 33:23.083
- Where are we going?
- The Holodeck.

33:25.837 --> 33:27.838
This is truly trying my patience,
counselor.

33:28.006 --> 33:30.257
l think you will approve.

33:30.425 --> 33:31.633
You're not coming in?

33:33.511 --> 33:35.053
No.

33:41.436 --> 33:42.978
Open.

33:59.328 --> 34:03.457
- An ascension ceremony.
LA FORGE: Happy anniversary, Worf.

34:04.625 --> 34:06.460
Shall we begin?

34:15.762 --> 34:17.137
l am ready.

34:24.270 --> 34:27.189
[WORF AND KLlNGONS
SPEAKlNG lN KLlNGON]

34:38.534 --> 34:41.703
Today l am a warrior.

34:41.871 --> 34:44.539
l must show you my heart.

34:44.707 --> 34:47.417
l travel the river of blood.

34:48.377 --> 34:50.170
[YELLlNG]

34:57.428 --> 34:59.471
The true test of Klingon strength

34:59.639 --> 35:02.390
is to admit
one's most profound feelings

35:02.558 --> 35:05.060
while under extreme duress.

35:08.064 --> 35:09.981
[WORF SPEAKS lN KLlNGON]

35:11.943 --> 35:14.027
[YELLlNG]

35:19.909 --> 35:22.119
The battle is mine.

35:22.578 --> 35:25.622
l crave only the blood of the enemy.

35:26.124 --> 35:27.624
[SPEAKS lN KLlNGON]

35:28.709 --> 35:30.836
[YELLlNG]

35:37.844 --> 35:43.223
The bile of the vanquished
flows over my hands.

35:43.808 --> 35:45.851
[SPEAKS lN KLlNGON]

35:47.770 --> 35:49.896
[YELLlNG]

35:59.574 --> 36:02.075
[WORF GRUNTlNG
AND PANTlNG]

36:11.460 --> 36:13.295
Thank you.

36:31.063 --> 36:34.107
- ls Lieutenant Worf all right?
- He's never been happier.

36:34.275 --> 36:35.942
So it was a good ceremony.

36:36.110 --> 36:40.197
Well, let's just say that l was not
about to stay around for refreshments.

36:40.364 --> 36:42.449
Klingon culture is not in your taste?

36:42.617 --> 36:44.910
l'm just glad
that humans have progressed

36:45.077 --> 36:47.829
beyond the need
for barbaric display.

36:48.539 --> 36:49.998
Have they?

36:50.166 --> 36:53.335
Commander Riker and his father
are in the gymnasium

36:53.502 --> 36:55.795
about to engage
in a barbarism of their own.

36:55.963 --> 36:58.965
Don't remind me. lt's something
of which l do not approve.

36:59.133 --> 37:00.675
ln spite of human evolution,

37:00.843 --> 37:04.054
there are still some traits
that are endemic to gender.

37:04.222 --> 37:06.389
You think they're going
to knock each other's brains out

37:06.557 --> 37:07.682
because they're men?

37:07.850 --> 37:09.809
Human males are unique.

37:09.977 --> 37:12.020
Fathers continue
to regard their sons as children

37:12.188 --> 37:15.148
even into adulthood,
and sons continue to chafe against

37:15.316 --> 37:18.235
what they perceive
is their father's expectations of them.

37:19.946 --> 37:23.031
lt's almost as if they never
really grow up at all, isn't it?

37:25.701 --> 37:30.914
Perhaps that's part of their charm
and why we find them so attractive.

37:31.457 --> 37:34.125
Particularly a man
like Commander Riker.

37:35.336 --> 37:37.337
And his father.

37:40.758 --> 37:43.218
l hope they don't injure each other.

37:48.182 --> 37:49.849
Anbo-jyutsu.

37:50.017 --> 37:53.186
The ultimate evolution
in the martial arts.

37:53.354 --> 37:55.563
l remember my early lessons.

37:55.731 --> 37:58.316
You could never get used
to the sightless factor.

37:58.484 --> 38:01.111
- Or to losing.
- True.

38:01.279 --> 38:03.571
But l've had 1 5 years to practice.

38:04.323 --> 38:08.368
Well, let's see
if you've learned anything.

38:12.957 --> 38:15.500
[BOTH SPEAK lN JAPANESE]

38:46.866 --> 38:48.283
[KYLE GRUNTS]

39:02.548 --> 39:04.174
Well...

39:08.304 --> 39:10.805
- You've been practicing.
- And remembering.

39:10.973 --> 39:14.517
You should have been the one to die,
not her.

39:15.019 --> 39:17.979
[RlKER SPEAKS lN JAPANESE]

39:18.147 --> 39:21.483
Good. Get it all out.

39:21.692 --> 39:23.777
[KYLE SPEAKS lN JAPANESE]

39:41.670 --> 39:43.296
[RlKER GRUNTS]

39:44.757 --> 39:46.341
[RlKER SPEAKS lN JAPANESE]

39:47.927 --> 39:49.928
l had you.

39:50.304 --> 39:54.391
Listen, Will, you were too young
to understand.

39:54.558 --> 39:56.935
And l was too hurt to explain.

39:57.103 --> 39:59.229
You were never too hurt
for anything.

39:59.397 --> 40:02.774
She was your mother.
But she was my wife.

40:02.942 --> 40:07.362
And when she died,
all that kept me going was you.

40:07.530 --> 40:09.697
You had a strange way
of showing it.

40:09.865 --> 40:12.409
l came here thinking
we could talk this out.

40:12.576 --> 40:13.868
But maybe you're right.

40:14.370 --> 40:17.122
Maybe l am no father.
And you're no son.

40:17.748 --> 40:20.834
And this fight is all we have left.

40:25.548 --> 40:26.923
[BOTH GRUNTlNG]

40:45.568 --> 40:46.985
RlKER:
Wait!

40:49.572 --> 40:50.613
What is it now?

40:51.699 --> 40:54.033
- You can't do that.
- What?

40:54.743 --> 40:55.785
[SPEAKS lN JAPANESE]

40:55.953 --> 40:57.912
[lN ENGLlSH]
lt's illegal.

40:58.080 --> 40:59.622
You're kidding.

41:01.625 --> 41:03.251
All these years.

41:03.419 --> 41:05.628
That's why l never won.
You were cheating.

41:06.464 --> 41:07.839
[CHUCKLES]

41:08.007 --> 41:10.008
lt worked, didn't it?

41:10.176 --> 41:12.594
Kept you coming back for more.

41:12.761 --> 41:14.762
lncredible.

41:14.930 --> 41:17.056
You cheated me.
How'd you get away with it?

41:17.224 --> 41:18.558
You were just a kid.

41:18.726 --> 41:21.144
By the time you were 1 2 years old,
l knew l couldn't take you.

41:21.312 --> 41:24.105
l had to keep you interested.
l had to keep you challenged, didn't l?

41:24.648 --> 41:27.400
- l always hated you for that.
- Damn it, Will!

41:27.568 --> 41:29.569
You were barely out of diapers
when she died.

41:29.737 --> 41:31.654
You hardly knew her.

41:31.822 --> 41:33.198
l loved her.

41:34.950 --> 41:37.243
Of course you carried the pain.
So did l.

41:37.411 --> 41:41.623
l should have explained this to you
a long time ago but it hurt too much.

41:43.834 --> 41:45.543
And then the wall grew up
between us.

41:46.212 --> 41:49.255
And living there, you and me,
the wall got bigger.

41:51.050 --> 41:52.509
You know,

41:53.344 --> 41:55.303
it's funny.

41:56.388 --> 41:59.057
l can talk to a whole room full
of admirals

41:59.225 --> 42:01.893
about anything in the galaxy,

42:02.728 --> 42:07.148
but l can't talk to you
about how l feel.

42:08.275 --> 42:10.443
How do you feel?

42:13.030 --> 42:15.156
How do you think?

42:16.659 --> 42:18.618
l love you, son.

42:24.083 --> 42:27.210
l've got to get back to, uh,
the starbase.

42:27.378 --> 42:28.836
l know.

42:29.296 --> 42:30.964
l'm glad you came.

42:36.887 --> 42:39.097
Be careful now, okay?

42:48.607 --> 42:50.567
Starbase Montgomery's
briefing specialist

